The paper discusses the performance measurement of cloud computing services, which involves distributed systems and network infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the use of network for data exchange, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as the second likely category. The paper also involves the creation of a HTTP service, which falls under the category cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of virtual resources and elastic virtual machines, which suggests the category cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of increasing the number of users on the quality of service, which involves system dynamics and control, suggesting the category cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible category.
